column2: Sunesis Pharmaceuticals, Inc. engages in the development and commercialization of new oncology therapeutics for the treatment of solid and hematologic cancers. The company is headquartered in South San Francisco, California and currently employs 29 full-time employees. The firm focuses on the development and commercialization of its pipeline of oncology therapeutics for the treatment of solid and hematologic cancers. The Companyâ€™s lead programs are Vecabrutinib, SNS-510 and TAK-580. The firm also offers Vosaroxin, an anticancer quinolone derivative (AQD), which is used for the treatment of acute myeloid leukemia (AML). Vecabrutinib is a selective, reversible, non-covalent binding inhibitor of Bruton's tyrosine kinase (BTK) inhibitors. SNS-510 is a phosphoinositide dependent protein kinase 1 (PDK1) inhibitors. TAK-580 is an oral, investigative drug selective for pan-Raf kinase inhibition, in patients with relapsed or refractory solid tumors.
